sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36719
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This system is design to hydroxylate medium-length alkanes (C5-C12). alkB1 codes for an alkane hydroxylating protein. rubA and rubB code for two other proteins to supply reducing electrons. Alkanols derived from this reaction are intermediates as plasticizers and solvents in chemical and pharmaceutical industries.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tammy Hsu, Ruby Lee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: alkB2, rubA1, rubA2 are from Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1. rubB is from Pseudomonas fluorescens Pf-5.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli RNA pol transcription terminator designed and tested by Guillaume Cambray at BIOFAB Emeryville. Based on the natural E. coli rnpB T1 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Guillaume Cambray et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36717
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: rubB catalyzes the conversion of rubredoxin from reduced to oxidized state.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tammy Hsu, Ruby Lee

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (strong), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: c/o Vivek Mutalik et al. BIOFAB Emeryville
